    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Economic Scene column in Business Day on Thursday, about the limitations of the current copyright law and proposals to fix it, misstated the year that changes in the law went into effect. It was 1978, not 1964. (Under the revised law, books published before 1964 could have their copyright renewed in the 28th year after their initial registration.)</p>
      </block>
